99/drivers-fuel-efficiency-red-light-habit-idling" data-article-image="https://cdn.images.express.co.uk/img/dynamic/24/285x169/1895499_1.jpg"> <svg width="25" height="25" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" data-bookmark-icon> <path d="M17 3H7C5.9 3 5 3.9 5 5V21L12 18L19 21V5C19 3.9 18.1 3 17 3Z" fill="rgba(0,0,0,0)"></path> <path d="M17 3H7C5.9 3 5 3.9 5 5V21L12 18L19 21V5C19 3.9 18.1 3 17 3ZM17 18L12 15.82L7 18V5H17V18Z" fill="#FFFFFF"></path> </svg> </span></div><h4>Drivers can increase fuel efficiency by avoiding a ‘red light’ bad habit - it's not idling</h4><p>Auto industry experts have explained how extra mileage can be won or lost at traffic stoplights...</p> </a></div></li></ul> </section><div class="box-container slot5 liftOdd"><div class="rh-element new box homepage type21" data-vr-zone="R/H Side More From The Pot (Latest News) 5"><div data-post-id="1895407" class="pure new short clearfix newmftp" data-vr-contentbox=""> <a class="" href="/life-style/cars/1895407/petrol-diesel-drivers-increase-fuel-efficiency" onclick="ExpressApp.GoogleAnalytics.TrackEvent('Latest News', 'petrol-diesel-drivers-increase-fuel-efficiency')"><div class="lazy-container"> <picture><source type="image/avif" srcset="https://cdn.images.express.co.uk/img/dynamic/24/183x122/1895407_1.avif"><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://cdn.images.express.co.uk/img/dynamic/24/183x122/1895407_1.webp"><img src="https://cdn.images.express.co.uk/img/dynamic/24/183x122/1895407_1.jpg" alt="petrol-diesel-drivers-increase-fuel-efficiency" title="petrol-diesel-drivers-increase-fuel-efficiency" width="183" height="122" loading="lazy"></picture> <span class="bookmark-icon" data-bookmark="0" data-article-id="1895407" data-article-headline="Petrol &amp; diesel drivers can increase fuel efficiency with a straightforward ‘45 mph’ rule" data-article-url="https://www.express.co.uk/life-style/cars/1895407/petrol-diesel-drivers-increase-fuel-efficiency" data-article-image="https